            <Field key="sec_vacancy"><Value>* United Kingdom Search/
     * EMEA VAT Manager, Manufacturing

EMEA VAT Manager, Manufacturing

   Location:
   Crawley
   Job Type:
   Permanent
   Ref:
   BBBH734407
   Salary:
   £50k - £60k
   Post date:
   25/06/2019 - 11:00
   Consultant:
   Emily Thomas

   A multinational manufacturing company is recruiting for an EMEA Tax Manager in a permanent job based in Crawley. This role will incorporate VAT compliance as well as Personal Tax filings and Transfer Pricing documentation.

   The company are a manufactoring giant with offices based in both Central London and in the South East. The company are offering progression and internal opportunities alongside a fantastic working environment. This EMEA VAT Manager job has come about through natural expansion and is an excellent opportunity to join a dynamic organization at an exciting time of their growth.

   Key Responsibilities:
     * Retrieving and ensuring Corporate and VAT reports are reviewed and submitted on time
     * Managing VAT and Income Tax payments to Tax Authorities
     * Managing VAT Account Reconciliations process
     * Determine Income Tax obligations where required to support the expanding supply chain
     * Performing contracts reviews and ensure tax language is appropriate
     * Providing Tax support with potential new supply chains
     * Communicating and coordinating VAT and Tax issues across all key stakeholders.

   About you:
     * Minimum of 5 years relevant VAT experience
     * You will have multinational experience and a good understanding of VAT compliance processes.
     * You will need to have the ability to identify VAT process weaknesses and implement process improvements.
     * You will also be able to demonstrate strong written and verbal communication skills.

   Morgan McKinley is acting as an Employment Agency in relation to this vacancy.

   Please note that any references to salary or pay rates in this advertisement and in the salary refinement section are indicative only and should only be used as a guide.

     * Apply for this job

